                <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/1278: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-28T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 28, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 28—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>298. For the Acting Secretary of State. Your 147, December 27, 1 p.m. In
                    compliance with your suggestion Aranha will immediately <pb facs="0254" n="245"
                        xml:id="pg_245"/> instruct Mello Franco to remain in Lima and endeavor to
                    obtain an agreement in principle between the Peruvian and Ecuadorean Foreign
                    Ministers. He will likewise instruct Mello Franco to keep in touch with the
                    American Ambassador there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
